  "notes": "Filipino/Tagalog standard orthography (Abakada + expanded 28-letter alphabet). Glottal stop /ʔ/ is phonemic but unwritten (word-initial vowels, mid-word, and some finals). Word-final K → [ʔ]. Intervocalic D → [ɾ]. NG = /ŋ/ (single phoneme, alphabetized as unit). Stress marked with tilde (˜) in formal texts. Vowel system: /a e i o u/ with /ɛ/ ~ /e/ and /o/ ~ /u/ merging in some varieties.",
